ate papers, Thomas elucidates the critical importance of the spaces around which women conceptualised alternative creative and professional lifestyles.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArts and crafts movementzGreat BritainxHistory. 0aWomen artisanszGreat BritainxHistory. 0aWomen artistszGreat BritainxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh  aArt.  aArts and Crafts movement.  aExpertise.  aGender.  aProfessions.  aSpace.  aSuffrage.  aUrban Culture.  aWomen.  aWork.1 aThomas, Zoë, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packagez978311128248040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614044940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526140449423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526140449/original  a978-3-11-128248-0  Manchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packageb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles